[4] Peru (Lima)
Date: Mon, 18 Apr 2005
From: "Martin Vasquez" <martin2050@gmail.com>

The General Office of Epidemiology announced 34 cases of dengue fever in
patients coming from district of Comas, city of Lima. The National Health
Institute confirmed cases by serology. The strain was typified as dengue
virus type III by polymerase chain reaction. The health authorities have
begun the spraying of 8000 houses in the outbreak area, along with active
surveillance of cases.
--
